---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Cody Smith — Web Management & Marketing Strategy">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-32 pb-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-amber-500 font-mono text-sm tracking-wider mb-6">Cedar City, Utah</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-stone-100 leading-tight mb-8">
        I keep websites running<br />
        and businesses<br class="hidden md:block" />
        moving forward.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-stone-400 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-12">
        Web management, marketing strategy, and training for companies that build things.
        I handle the digital infrastructure so you can focus on the work that matters.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
        <a href="/services" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 bg-amber-600 text-stone-950 font-medium text-sm rounded hover:bg-amber-500 transition-colors">
          See how I work
        </a>
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 border border-stone-700 text-stone-300 font-medium text-sm rounded hover:border-stone-500 hover:text-stone-100 transition-colors">
          Get in touch
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I do -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 border-t border-stone-800/50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-100 mb-12">Four lanes. One practice.</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="p-6 rounded-lg border border-stone-800/50 hover:border-stone-700 transition-colors">
          <h3 class="text-stone-100 font-medium mb-2">Web Management</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Hosting, security, performance, updates, monitoring. Monthly health reports that prove the work is happening. Your site runs — I make sure it keeps running.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 rounded-lg border border-stone-800/50 hover:border-stone-700 transition-colors">
          <h3 class="text-stone-100 font-medium mb-2">Marketing Strategy</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            SEO, competitive analysis, content direction, keyword strategy. I tell you what to do and why — then help you measure whether it worked.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 rounded-lg border border-stone-800/50 hover:border-stone-700 transition-colors">
          <h3 class="text-stone-100 font-medium mb-2">Implementation</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Site migrations, integrations, page builds, analytics setup. The project work that changes production systems. Scoped, quoted, delivered.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 rounded-lg border border-stone-800/50 hover:border-stone-700 transition-colors">
          <h3 class="text-stone-100 font-medium mb-2">Training</h3>
          <p class="text-stone-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            WordPress, SEO, AI workflows. Built on learning science, not slide decks. Your team leaves knowing how to do the work — not just what the work is.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The pitch -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 border-t border-stone-800/50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-100 mb-8">The short version.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-stone-400 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Most small businesses don't need a marketing department. They need one person who understands the whole picture — someone who can look at the website, the analytics, the SEO, the content, and the competitive landscape, and tell them what actually matters this month.
        </p>
        <p>
          That's what I do. I've spent a career absorbing adjacent problems — writing that turned into web strategy, web strategy that turned into marketing operations, marketing operations that turned into training programs. Every role, the same pattern: start with the thing I was hired for, end up doing the three things nobody else was handling.
        </p>
        <p>
          Now I do it on purpose.
        </p>
      </div>
      <a href="/about" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-amber-500 text-sm mt-8 hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors">
        Read the longer version
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
